This was evident on 16 September when the new president had to be elected.
The delegates of the General Assembly met in vain at the National House (Národní dům), located in the Prague district of Smíchov, because the talks had been blocked and not only regarding the election method.
There was no consensus on who in the General Assembly had the right to vote - only the legal representatives or also the delegates with full powers.
From that point onwards, and because of this single point, a partial agreement was reached, supported also by the recommendation of the Institute of State and Law, according to which full representation is not possible.
