"The dispute is whether to proceed according to the statutes or to find another model", says Dušan Svoboda, one of the three vice-presidents of the FAČR, who, from the association's leadership, represents professional football.
According to the model proposed in the statutes, in the third round the candidate with the highest percentage of support in the federation to which he will submit his candidacy will win.
The Moravian Region is ready to reach a compromise so that it can win that candidate with a higher percentage of total votes in both federations.
The Bohemian side, however, imposes the condition that the winner, according to these percentage calculations, must have a majority of at least two thirds.
