Austria thus responds to a request from the Brussels Summit to the euro area member countries on 26 October: in it, the Heads of State or Government called for the inclusion, before the end of 2012, of the reduction of the public deficit and the recovery of the balance of public accounts in the Constitution or in a law with equivalent value.
The Austrian Government's approach is similar to the German model, as Germany was the first European country to adopt such a 'rule'.
By 2017, the structural public deficit should decrease by 0.75% of gross domestic product (GDP) each year and, from 2017, the structural public deficit of the federal state should not exceed 0.35% of GDP each year, while regional states, as well as municipalities, should present balanced budgets.
