We will not win if we demand a succession of national referendums, organised according to needs and in a disorderly way.
A blank signature to the absolute European monarch or a stop to the vacuum of the nationalist hole: what options for the citizen!
We are not trying to take a coup, but a common, full, peaceful and continuous exercise of choices and democracy, this time at European level.
There is no crisis in Greece, Italy, Spain, Portugal (in fact, we wouldn't know where to end the list), because there is only one crisis, the crisis of Europe.
The whole of Europe is one which follows the orders of markets and rating agencies, one which suffers from its impotence and lack of solidarity.
It is Europe as a whole that is being humiliated in the international arena.
We are concerned about the transfer of sovereignty to Europe, but it is all of Europe that is slowly losing sovereignty and with it every one of its nations.
The most urgent thing is that the people's sovereignty regains the helm of the European project.
Because only together can Europeans reduce their debt burden, free themselves from markets and prepare their future through investment.
The crisis will require decisions at European level that cannot be taken without full democratic legitimacy, unless they lead to disaster.
After a long struggle against this proposal by the Socialists and Jacques Delors, everyone is now calling for European economic governance.
Let it be.
But to think of it without greater political and democratic integration, and without it being lived as such by citizens, would be a new madness and would lead us to a new stalemate.
We must take on a new stage in European construction.
To build the Republic in France, it was necessary to "make" Republicans.
An interest-driven revolution would not be enough.
This lesson is still applicable.
We must build a more economically integrated Europe.
Only by building a more democratic Europe at the political level, a true European popular sovereignty, can this be achieved.
To build Europe, let us make it European.
